# ============================================================================
# Paydirt - Demonstration Log File
# Machine Data Insights Inc. | machinedatainsights.com
# ============================================================================
#
# Purpose: A single file exercising every scrubbing category Paydirt and
# log_scrubber.py handle. Drop this into Paydirt to verify that every
# category of sensitive data gets redacted correctly, plus that a set of
# deliberately-safe strings are left alone (negative test cases).
#
# How to use:
#   1. Open Paydirt.html in your browser
#   2. Drop this file onto the drop zone (or click "choose files")
#   3. Click the "Comparison" tab on the result card
#   4. Scroll through each section and verify that the scrubbed side shows
#      the expected redactions from each category
#
# Each section below is marked with a "# SECTION N:" header describing what
# the section demonstrates. The section headers are themselves comments,
# so they pass through unscrubbed and serve as landmarks in the output.
#
# Sections labeled "NEGATIVE TEST CASES" contain entries that LOOK like
# they should be scrubbed but shouldn't be. If those survive intact, the
# scrubber is behaving correctly (not over-scrubbing).
#
# ============================================================================


