# ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# SECTION 22: Controlled Unclassified Information markings (CMMC / NIST SP 800-171)
# Expect: the entire line redacted to a placeholder. Unlike the other
# categories, compliance markings cause whole-line redaction because the
# marking itself is the signal that everything nearby is sensitive.
#
# Paydirt detects four marking styles (shown in the data lines below):
#   - Banner style: the uppercase form of the control, with optional suffix
#   - Portion markings: parenthesized with an in-line classification token
#   - Legacy tags: the short acronyms used before the 2010 executive order
#   - Adjacent classifications: export-control and defense-industry tags
# ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
CUI//SP-PRVCY Employee record: John Smith DOB 1980-01-15 SSN 123-45-6789
CONTROLLED//SP-PROPIN Contract pricing detail for vendor bid submitted 2026-02-01
(U//FOUO) Internal memo: merger discussions with target company scheduled for Q3
FOUO: staff meeting notes regarding upcoming reorganization attached
ITAR-controlled export specification for defense article classification 3A980
SBU: personnel action regarding employee ID 4491 pending HR review


